+Verify Project Name: Ensure that the project_name used in your deployment code matches exactly with how it is set up in Azure. Based on your transaction, check if the project name is indeed "midnight" or another name specified during the setup.
+
+Use the Correct Model Parameter: If you are invoking a specific OpenAI model (like "gpt-4o"), confirm that this model is properly set up and is supported by your Azure OpenAI instance. Cross-check that gpt-4o is available according to your deployment setup and within the allowed models[17:4].
+
+Endpoint Configuration: Update your Azure configuration to ensure you are using the correct endpoint:
+
+project_endpoint = "https://midnight.openai.azure.com/"
+Check for Agent Specifications: Ensure that the agent creation parameters align with what the Azure service expects. For example:
+
+The instructions provided must be valid and within any character limits set by Azure.
+The deployment name ("gpt-4o") should match an existing deployment.
+Look for Additional Errors: Check if there are any errors or diagnostic messages in the Azure portal under the activity logs related to the Cognitive Services resource. This may provide insight into the issue during the agent creation process.
+
+Permissions and Role: Confirm that you have the necessary permissions to create agents within the resource. You should have sufficient privileges assigned in the Azure role.
+
+Resource Location: Confirm that your model and agent are both in the same location (in this case, "eastus"). If they are in different locations, you might face connectivity issues.
